<h1>Paris</h1>
<p>Paris is the capital city of France and one of the most famous and visited cities in the world. Located on the banks of the River Seine in northern France, Paris is known for its rich history, stunning architecture, and as a global center for art, fashion, and culture.</p>

<p>Paris has a history dating back over two thousand years. Originally a small settlement founded by the Parisii, a Celtic tribe, it grew into a major city during the Roman era. The city became the capital of the Frankish Kingdom in the 5th century and has remained the political, cultural, and intellectual center of France ever since.</p>

<p>The city is renowned for its iconic landmarks such as the Eiffel Tower, the Louvre Museum, the Notre-Dame Cathedral, and the Champs-Élysées. Paris is also famous for its world-class cuisine, with countless bistros, cafés, and patisseries offering French specialties like croissants, escargot, and crème brûlée.</p>

